---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const updated = '2026-04-05';
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Service — Crontinel"
  description="Crontinel Terms of Service."
>
  <Nav />

  <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-10">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-base mb-2">1. Acceptance</h2>
        <p>By using Crontinel (crontinel.com and app.crontinel.com) you agree to these terms. If you don't agree, do not use the service.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-base mb-2">2. The service</h2>
        <p>Crontinel is a Laravel monitoring service. We provide cron job monitoring, queue monitoring, and Horizon health monitoring via a SaaS platform and an open-source package.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-base mb-2">3. Your account</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
          <li>You are responsible for maintaining your account credentials</li>
          <li>You must provide accurate information at registration</li>
          <li>You may not share accounts or use one account to represent multiple unrelated organizations</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-base mb-2">4. Billing</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
          <li>Paid subscriptions are billed monthly or annually in advance</li>
          <li>The 14-day trial requires no payment method</li>
          <li>Downgrades take effect at the end of the current billing period</li>
          <li>No refunds except where required by law</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-base mb-2">5. Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>You may not use Crontinel to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 mt-2">
          <li>Monitor applications you do not own or have permission to monitor</li>
          <li>Attempt to circumvent rate limits or abuse the API</li>
          <li>Violate any applicable law or regulation</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-base mb-2">6. Service availability</h2>
        <p>We aim for high availability but do not guarantee uptime. Crontinel is not liable for missed alerts or monitoring gaps caused by service downtime.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-base mb-2">7. Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>Crontinel is provided "as is." To the maximum extent permitted by law, we are not liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from use of the service.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-base mb-2">8. Termination</h2>
        <p>You may cancel your account at any time from your profile settings. We may terminate accounts that violate these terms.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-base mb-2">9. Changes</h2>
        <p>We may update these terms. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance. We'll notify you by email for material changes.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-base mb-2">10. Contact</h2>
        <p><a href="mailto:support@crontinel.com" class="text-gray-300 hover:text-white">support@crontinel.com</a></p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Base>
